Class Conditional

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.syst3ms.skriptparser.lang.Statement

        • io.github.syst3ms.skriptparser.lang.Conditional
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SyntaxElement

    public class Conditional
extends CodeSection
    A code section representing a condition. It can either be :
    • An "if" condition
    • An "else if" condition
    • An "else" condition, that does not include any condition
    This "mode" is described by a Conditional.ConditionalMode value, accessible through getMode(). This is the only syntax element to be understood natively by the parser.
    See Also:
    Conditional.ConditionalMode

      • init

        public boolean init(Expression<?>[] expressions,
                    int matchedPattern,
                    ParseContext parseContext)
        Description copied from interface: SyntaxElement
        Initialises this SyntaxElement before being used. This method is always called before all the others in an extending class, the only exception being CodeSection.loadSection(FileSection, io.github.syst3ms.skriptparser.log.SkriptLogger).
        Parameters:
        expressions - an array of expressions representing all the expressions that are being passed to this syntax element. As opposed to Skript, elements of this array can't be null.
        matchedPattern - the index of the pattern that was successfully matched. It corresponds to the order of the syntaxes in registration
        parseContext - an object containing additional information about the parsing of this syntax element, like regex matches and parse marks
        Returns:
        true if the syntax element was initialized successfully, false otherwise.
        See Also:
        SkriptRegistration, ParseContext
